        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 2 at 9:37PM PDT until July 2 at 10:00PM PDT by NWS Las Vegas NV</headline>
        <description>At 936 PM PDT, a severe thunderstorm was located just southeast of
Shoshone, moving north at 15 mph. This storm has intensified, and is
almost certainly producing large hail.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind damage
to roofs and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Shoshone and Tecopa.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
